Commentary Text: Shakib to Chris Lynn, out Caught by Rashid Khan!! That looked ugly, but Shakib has his man. A pre-empted charge from Lynn, Shakib saw it coming and fired the slider - kept coming with the angle and cramped Lynn for room - he looked very awkward as he tried to force it away - off the toe-end of the bat and scooped in the air towards cover-point. Rashid under the ball and he doesn't drop those. Chris Lynn c Rashid Khan b Shakib 7(11) [6s-1]
